VP can be expressed using variables and common
events, separate from those directly input for SE
and screen effects.

By inputting the corresponding variables in
925~928 and executing Common Events 391~394, you
can play SEs that match each situation.

If you want to repeat an SE, it will repeat for
the number of times entered in variable 932 (the
repeated SE will play a random appropriate SE).

For flashes and screen effects, you can express
them by executing variable 933 and Common Event
397.

For details, please refer to the relevant section
of the "About Modifications" item in recent ci-en
articles.

Besides this, you can also continuously play sound
effects using BGS, so feel free to create events
without being limited to the above functions.

I've compiled a simple list of various SEs that
seem likely to be used for copy-pasting.

Currently, VP is in a very unstable operating
environment, and when saving data, it crashes
about once every two times.

Therefore, before saving, you need to save the
created event information externally, or else you
won't be able to proceed with work properly.

One way to do this is to run Tsukuru twice, using
one for event creation and the other for primary
data saving to prevent accidents due to forced
termination.
